MAY 31 - JUNE 2
ARTFEST 2002 will be held on the grounds of the Northwest Museum of Arts and Culture, 2316 West First Avenue, Spokane.
This event features three days of arts, crafts, music, food and fun.
There will be juried artists, food booths, hands-on activities, and artist demonstrations.
Concerts will be conducted on the music stage on Friday and Saturday nights.
Admission is FREE.
For more information, contact Heather Snow at (509) 363-5301.
