JUNE 7-9, FRIDAY - SUNDAY
PAGDIRIWANG 2002.
The Filipino Cultural Heritage Society will present this celebration at the Seattle Center House.
Pagdiriwang is a Filipino history, cultural and arts festival, this year celebrating the 104th anniversary of Philippine independence.
From the "antique to avant-guard," the rich cultural heritage of the Philippines is showcased, including music, dance and visual arts.
Enjoy delicious food, games, and activities for the whole family as well as performances and workshops by artists from the Philippines and the U. S.
For more information, please call Seattle Center Customer Services at (206) 684-7200.
