Mary Campbell
The Service Quality Network will meet from 10:30 a.m. to 12:00 noon in the DSHS Headquarters, OB-2 Auditorium, 14th 
The topic "Quality-Aligning for Performance" will be presented by Mary Campbell, the newly appointed Special Assistant to the Governor for Quality and Performance in Government.
Mary will be sharing her impression about the progress state agencies have made in the last few years as well as her vision for Washington's Quality Initiative.
Prior to her recent appointment, Mary was the Internal Quality Consultant for the Washington State Library, where she supported management and teams in the implementation of the Baldrige principles in the context of a team-based organization.
Contact person: Kathy Williams (360) 486-3440, ext. 3457.
